msgid ""
"The universal webcam control center for Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam was born as a small shell script so that Rafael Ruscher could use his Canon Rebel T3 as a "
"webcam during live streams about BigLinux. That humble hack, written by Rafael and Barnabé di "
"Kartola, evolved from a Bash bridge between gPhoto2 and FFmpeg into a full GTK4/Adwaita application "
"with live preview, multi-backend camera support (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP cameras, "
"smartphones), real-time OpenCV effects, virtual camera output, photo and video capture, and 29 "
"languages."
msgstr ""
"Üks universaalne veebikaamera juhtimiskeskus Linuxile.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam sündis väikese shell-skripti kujul, et Rafael Ruscher saaks kasutada oma Canon Rebel T3 "
"veebikaamerana BigLinuxi otseülekannete ajal. See tagasihoidlik häkk, mille kirjutasid Rafael ja "
"Barnabé di Kartola, arenes Bash-sillast gPhoto2 ja FFmpeg'i vahel täieõiguslikuks GTK4/Adwaita "
"rakenduseks, millel on reaalajas eelvaade, mitme tagapõhja kaameratoe (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, "
"PipeWire, IP kaamerad, nutitelefonid), reaalajas OpenCV efektid, virtuaalne kaamera väljund, foto- "
"ja videovõte ning 29 keelt."
